cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the vulnerability of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to adversarial attacks and proposes a method to improve the resistance of CNNs to such attacks by selecting intelligent hyperparameters. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, since the paper discusses the impact of hyperparameters on the model's ability to resist attacks, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
